Content:: Keith Webster (born August 31, 1937) is a retired Canadian football player who played for the Winnipeg Blue Bombers. He won the Grey Cup with Winnipeg in 1959.[1] He played junior football with Daniel McIntyre Collegiate Institute in Winnipeg, previously.
